# CI & Pre-Commit Discipline

- Mirror CI locally with pre-commit: black, ruff, flake8, mypy, pytest with coverage.
- Default coverage threshold is enforced by CI; keep tests ≥ configured value.
- GitHub Actions: ubuntu-latest, Python 3.10 on PRs; full matrix only on releases.
- After triggering CI, wait ~2 minutes before checking status.

References: [pyproject.toml](mdc:pyproject.toml), [.coveragerc](mdc:.coveragerc)

# Tests & CI Parity

- Run: black, ruff, flake8, mypy, pytest with coverage before pushing.
- Mirror CI locally; investigate xenon/importlinter/deptry failures.
- Skip optional-extras tests when deps absent (e.g., streamlit/plotly).
- After triggering CI, wait ~2 minutes before checking status.
